<span id="vi.iv.x.i-p3"></span><span class="c9"><span
id="vi.iv.x.i-p3.1"></span>And</span> on the fourth day of our stay in
Tyre, <span id="fr_1079"></span>[1080](#fn_1079.md) Peter went out about
daybreak, and there met him not a few of the dwellers round about, with
very many of the inhabitants of Tyre itself, who cried out, and said,
“God through you have mercy upon us, God through you heal us!”  And
Peter stood on a high stone, that all might see him; and having greeted
them in a godly manner, thus began:—

